cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry (point set embeddability) and presents an algorithmic solution. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques such as range search and presents a generalized version of the problem, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents a complete characterization of the problem on a special class of graphs, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
